{
  "texts": [
    "(H)DPGMM models both the hyperdistribution and the individual posterior distributions with DPGMMs, linking them in a hierarchical fashion by making use of the set of available individual event posterior distributions Y = {y 1,.",
    ", y N }; hence the name 'hierarchy of Dirichlet process Gaussian mixture models'.",
    "The posterior distribution then reads p(Θ|Y) ∝ j p(x j |Θ) p(x j |θ j) p(θ j |y j) p(Θ) dθ j dx i,",
    "where both p(x j |Θ) and p(x j |θ j) are DPGMMs.",
    "Here, θ j denotes the DPGMM parameters of the jth event and Θ denotes the DPGMM parameters {w, µ, σ} for the hyperdistribution."
  ]
}